CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1955, pg. A8 reads: "NAACP Protest Rally: 3,000 Hear Emmett Till Case Facts; Give; Urge United States to Act - Not walking Alone - Scores of the hundreds in audience greeted Dr. and Mrs. Howard to assure them that they are not walking alone in the fight against Mississippi's injustice to Negroes."
TitMainTitle: Dr. T. R. M. Howard shaking hands with woman with others, including Helen Howard wearing striped jacket, and men looking on, on stage of Soldier's and Sailor's Memorial Hall for NAACP protest rally
